Up 
delete /invocation/{id}
Cancel a workflow invocation (cancel)
This action is irreverisble. A canceled invocation cannot be resumed or restarted. In case that an invocation already is canceled, has failed or has completed, nothing happens. In case that an invocation does not exist a HTTP 404 error status is returned.

get /invocation/{id}
Get the specification and status of a workflow invocation (get)
Get returns three different aspects of the workflow invocation, namely the spec (specification), status and logs. To lighten the request load, consider using a more specific request.

typesFnRef - Up

FnRef is an immutable, unique reference to a function on a specific function runtime environment.

The string representation (via String or Format): runtime://runtimeId

runtime (optional)
String Runtime is the Function Runtime environment (fnenv) that was used to resolve the function.
namespace (optional)
String Namespace is the namespace of the fission function.
ID (optional)
String ID is the runtime-specific identifier of the function.

typesObjectMetadata - Up

ObjectMetadata contains common metadata present for all objects in the workflow engine.

It closely follows the structure of Kubernetes' ObjectMetadata, leaving out the parameters that do not fit the workflow model, such as namespaces, clusters, finalizers, etc. In the future, if it fits the model, we may move to using Kubernetes' ObjectMetadata directly.

id (optional)
String
name (optional)
String Name is an optional human-readable name of the object.
createdAt (optional)
Date Created at contains the timestamp of when this object was created. Typically the updatedAt field can be found in the status of the object. format: date-time
generation (optional)
String Generation is a sequence identifier used and updated by the system to record the number of events or changes applied to the object. format: int64

typesTaskStatusStatus - Up

typesTypedValue - Up

TypedValue is used to serialize, deserialize, transfer data values across the workflow engine.

It consists partly copy of protobuf's Any, to avoid protobuf requirement of a protobuf-based type.

type (optional)
String Type is an arbitrary string representation of a type. Each type has an associated parser/formatter.
value (optional)
byte[] Value holds the actual value in an arbitrary serialized form. A parser should be able to parse this format based on the type. format: byte
labels (optional)
map[String, String] Labels hold metadata about the value. It is used for example to store origins of data, past transformations, and information needed by serialization processes.

typesWorkflowSpec - Workflow Definition Up

The workflowDefinition contains the definition of a workflow.

Ideally the source code (json, yaml) can be converted directly to this message. Naming, triggers and versioning of the workflow itself is out of the scope of this data structure, which is delegated to the user/system upon the creation of a workflow.

apiVersion (optional)
String apiVersion describes what version is of the workflow definition. By default the workflow engine will assume the latest version to be used.
tasks (optional)
map[String, typesTaskSpec]

Tasks contains the specs of the tasks, with the key being the task id.

Note: Dependency graph is build into the tasks.

outputTask (optional)
String
description (optional)
String
forceId (optional)
String The UID that the workflow should have. Only use this in case you want to force a specific UID.
name (optional)
String
internal (optional)
Boolean Internal indicates whether is a workflow should be visible to a human (default) or not. format: boolean
